Definition: usually plural) the state of having reflex spasms of the diaphragm accompanied by a rapid closure of the glottis producing an audible sound
Example: sometimes a symptom of indigestion; how do you cure the hiccups?
Synonyms: verb, body, hiccough, singultus, symptom, noun, act, reflex, communication, plural, u, usually, the, state, of, having, spasms, diaphragm, accompanied, by, a, rapid, closure, glottis, producing, an, audible, sound, sometimes, indigestion, how, do, you, cure, hiccups
Category: noun.state
